<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{4}{y}={12}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{4}{y}=-{28}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({4},{1}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{4}{y}={12}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}={12}-{\left({4}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{12}-{\left({4}{y}\right)}}}{{2}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{\left(\frac{{{12}-{\left({4}{y}\right)}}}{{2}}\right)}+-{4}{y}=-{28}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{6}}{{2}}\cdot{\left({12}\right)}--\frac{{6}}{{2}}{\left({4}\right)}{y}+-{4}{y}=-{28}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{36}-{\left({12}\right)}{y}+-{4}{y}=-{28}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{12}{y}+{\left(-{4}\right)}{y}=-{28}--{36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{12}{y}+{\left(-{4}\right)}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({12}+{\left(-{4}\right)}\right)}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{8}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={1}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{4}{\left({1}\right)}={12}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{\left({4}\right)}={12}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}={12}-{\left({4}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{8}}{{2}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={4}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({4},{1}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

